args: I have returned. And it seems...
*sigh* I can't believe the two of you\nfollowed me all the way here.
But of course! It is our most earnest wish\nto accompany you, Master Xuan Zang!
I'll follow you to the ends of the earth or \nthe middle of an enemy camp to repay\neverything I owe you!
While I...appreciate the sentiment,\nI have no intentions of allowing\noutsiders to accompany me.
I suggest you give up and accept it.\nNow if you'll pardon me?
Aw, c'mon! She oughta let you join up!\nA lively trip is way more fun, yeah?
Heavens above and worms below!\nYou're Qilin! Might you also have\na relic with you, perchance?
Huh? You're into relics? Oh man,\nthat is a piece of good news!
I got relics comin' out the... Well, I got\na whole lotta relics. C'mon up to my\nroom, and I'll show ya my wares!
OOOOOOO! What a dollop of delight\nthis will prove to be!
...I see. So your goal is to use relics to\ngive people a more convenient life?
Yep. I've got all these useful dealies here,\nso it'd be a waste not to use 'em!
Yes! YEEEES! You are absolutely right!\nIt is exactly as you say!

I myself have always thought the same!
Only a fool would seal relics away willy-
nilly simply because they are ＂dangerous＂
or ＂deadly＂ or ＂cause terrible maiming.＂
The generations march onward BECAUSE\nwe develop and research technology!
See, you get it! Though I mostly love it\n'cause I get to try out all sorts of stuff.
Yeah, I like you, man. You get me.
My skin crawls with delight, milady!
(What a stroke of good luck to meet such\nan understanding member of the Qilin!)
(It genuinely makes me consider switching\nfrom Master Xuan Zang's side... Hee hee!)
Hey, so what kinda relic do you\nwant to check out first? I got tons.
A most earth-shattering one!\nA relic that oozes with power!
Yes! In fact, I would be delighted to see\na phenomenon that surpasses all\nhuman comprehension!
Heh. So you REALLY wanna go over the\ntop, eh? In that caaaaase...

There's a relic called the Yong Run Hu that
creates an endless amount of water,
but this one takes that ability and
cranks it up to eleven!
It spurts out MASSIVE amounts of water!\nWe're talking waterfalls!
All that from such a small pot? My word!\nWhat sort of mechanism powers it?
I must disassemble it and... No, but that\nwould only destroy the precious relic.
Hee hee! You're a funny guy, pal!\nI like you even more now!
All right, let's go outside and see all the\ncrazy stuff the Hao Pu Hu can do!
Excitement leaks out of my\nevery nook and cranny, milady!
Hee hee! Yeah, I'm pretty great, all right.\nNow let's do this thing!

O power universal of the Qilin,
be bound by my solemn decree.
Billowing falls! Torrent of the river!
Invoke your gift strong and swift!
By the moon and sun!\nThis is like the great falls of Taiwu!
What a truly awesome amount of water!\nIn the blink of an eye, everything around\nus is...squishy...and damp...and flooded?
The water isn't in the castle yet,\nso I think we're still okay.
Huh? What happened to you two?\nAnd why are you both so wet?!
Oh, nothing! Just fiddling around\nwith a relic in the ol' courtyard!\nLa de dum de do...
The only good thing about this situation\nis that you both still draw breath.
Let me guess, Jiang Ziya: You got carried\naway with a relic and failed to seal it.
Oh man, I really screwed up this time.
Fascinating! So even a member of the\ngreat Qilin can make such a blunder?
(I never thought to meet a careless\nmember of their tribe... It's a lucky thing\nindeed that I did not switch allegiances!)
Well, this is certainly quite the problem\nyou two created. The courtyard is a lake,\nand I've no idea how to reach the relic.
We can stop the relic if we get close to it,\nyes? In that case, all we need are my wits\nand Zhu Bajie's hulking strength!
I do not wish to involve non-sealer\noutsiders in an incident caused by a relic.
Jiang Ziya and I will solve this alone.
Okay, that doesn't make ANY sense.
I mean, yeah, we're not sealers—\nbut we're also not outsiders.
We're all allies in this castle.
And this is putting all our allies in danger.\nSo if we don't save 'em, it's the same\nas if we never fulfilled our duty.
One can always count on Zhu Bajie to\nspew forth about honor and duty and...\nWell, all the rest of that.
My reasons are simpler: We have the\nknowledge and technology to solve\nthe problem, therefore we should.
And if we also save lives as a result,\nI suppose that's all right.
It couldn't hurt to get their help, right?\nWe're all on the same page here.
I will accept your help—both of you.
Whoa! The water's flooding outside\nthrough that hole he made in the wall!

Water will always flow from high places
to lower places. And as this courtyard is
the lowest spot in the castle, we need
only to make a hole, aaaand...
Hah! This is great stuff!\nIt's like unclogging a bath!
Now, Jiang Ziya! Stop the relic!

Gotcha! O power universal of the Qilin,
be bound by my solemn decree.
Billowing falls! Torrent of the river!
May your exertions be suppressed!
We should be all right now.\nThank you, both of you.
And if I may ask one more thing,\nwould you continue lending me\nyour combined strength?
I could use fellow travelers like you\non my quest to seal the relics.
